Function Reference/is random header image « WordPress Codex
-----------

Check if random header image is in use.

Always true if user expressly chooses the option in Appearance \>
Header. Also true if theme has multiple header images registered, no
specific header image is chosen, and theme turns on random headers with
add\_theme\_support().

Usage
-----

` <?php is_random_header_image( $type ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$type` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*default*) The random pool to use. any
    Default: uploaded

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(boolean)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   

Change Log
----------

Since: [3.2](/Version_3.2 "Version 3.2")

Source File
-----------

`is_random_header_image()` is located in `wp-includes/theme.php`

